nekobox-void
============
Void Linux packages for NekoBox (NyameBox), a cross-platform Qt proxy utility
powered by sing-box.

NekoBox provides a graphical interface for managing proxy configurations with
support for multiple protocols including SOCKS, HTTP(S), Shadowsocks, Trojan,
VMess, VLESS, TUIC, Hysteria, WireGuard, and more.

Upstream: https://github.com/qr243vbi/nekobox

Installing
----------
There are two options: use the repository for automatic updates, or install
the package manually with each release.

* Option 1. Repository (Recommended)
Create the file `/etc/xbps.d/20-nekobox.conf` with the following content:
repository=https://github.com/lion-lef/nekobox-void/releases/latest/download/

Then install with:
# xbps-install -Su nekobox

* Option 2. Manual Installation
Download a release (*.xbps) into an empty folder, then run:
$ cd <folder>
$ xbps-rindex -a nekobox-<version>_<revision>.<arch>.xbps
# xbps-install -R $PWD nekobox

Building
--------
Clone `void-packages` and bootstrap:
$ git clone https://github.com/void-linux/void-packages
$ cd void-packages
$ ./xbps-src binary-bootstrap

Clone this repository and copy the `nekobox-void/srcpkgs/nekobox` folder
into `void-packages/srcpkgs`, then run:
$ ./xbps-src pkg nekobox

Lastly, install with:
# xbps-install -R hostdir/binpkgs nekobox

Note:
If your `void-packages` or bootstrap is stale, update first:
$ cd void-packages
$ git pull origin master
$ ./xbps-src bootstrap-update

Dependencies
------------
The package requires:
- Qt6 base libraries
- Qt6 Wayland support (optional, for Wayland sessions)
- libfuse2 (for running in certain modes)

Build dependencies (handled automatically by xbps-src):
- cmake, ninja (build system)
- go (for sing-box core)
- thrift (for RPC code generation)
- qt6-base-devel, qt6-tools (Qt development files)

Supported Protocols
-------------------
NekoBox supports an extensive range of proxy protocols:
- SOCKS4/SOCKS5, HTTP(S)
- Shadowsocks
- Trojan
- VMess, VLESS
- TUIC, Hysteria, Hysteria2
- WireGuard
- SSH
- ShadowTLS, AnyTLS
- Mieru
- Tor (via external Tor process)
- TUN mode (requires root)
- Custom outbound configurations

Integrity
---------
The build process is fully transparent and package integrity can be verified
using the checksums displayed in the GitHub Actions build logs.

Verify a downloaded package against the log:
$ sha256sum nekobox-<version>_<revision>.<arch>.xbps

This manual check is necessary for integrity as GitHub Releases are mutable.

